{"word":"G989 - βλάσφημος - blásphēmos - blas'-fay-mos - Blasphemer","slug":"G989","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">βλάσφημος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>blásphēmos"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>blas'-fay-mos"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Blasphemer"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B2;&#x03BB;&#x03B1;&#x0301;&#x03C3;&#x03C6;&#x03B7;&#x03BC;&#x03BF;&#x03C2; - blasphe&#x0304;mos</b> - <i>blas'-fay-mos</i><p/>From a derivative of <a href=\"#/G984\">G984</a> and <a href=\"#/G5345\">G5345</a>; <i>scurrilous</i>, that is, <i>calumnious</i> (against man), or (specifically) <i>impious</i> (against God): - blasphemer (-mous), railing."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G987\">G987</a>, <a href=\"#/G988\">G988</a>"}]}